                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I return you many thanks for the<lb/> perusal of the enclosed, you\n                see I have read it with<lb/> parcel in hand, and have taken the liberty of<lb/>\n                making some passages where the omission of words<lb/> would I think strengthen &amp;\n                improve the style.</p>\n            <p>There is a little obscurity about the introduction<lb/> of the 139th Psalm did that\n                apt quotation immed<lb/>iately follow the beautiful lives to which it\n                    <sic>applys</sic><lb/> the whole would be much more impressive<lb/> he would not\n                stop to <sic>enquire</sic> if the history of<lb/> the cholera verifies scripture.\n                When the facts you<lb/> stole seem as if they might have inspired<lb/> the holy king\n                with those <add>?</add> of eloquent<lb/> subscription and deep\n                    conviction<add>?</add> of the omnipotence<lb/> of God if I did not know that you\n                are in the habit<lb/> of writing rapidly, and not revising before you submit<lb/>\n                your manuscripts I should be different of giving an<lb/> opinion because you would\n                be certainly a better<lb/> judge but <add>?</add> sometimes places the\n                    stress<add>?</add><lb/> into the hands of the weak and you see how<lb/> they\n                take advantage of it â€”</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(7)\">believe me very sincerely</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(7)\">your friend <persName role=\"author\">R G</persName></p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n"
                  },
